# LockIn General Preferences

- Keep code minimal and consistent with existing project patterns.
- Reuse existing functions and classes when possible; avoid unnecessary wrappers.
- Avoid overengineering and avoid creating many template classes for future features.
- Ask before modifying large chunks of code.
- Keep functions clean and straightforward.
- Prefer simple datatypes and ADTs.
- Avoid `CopyOnWrite*` and `Consumer`-style patterns when a simpler option works.
- Do not use Java `record`.
- Do not use nested classes.
- Keep comments minimal; prefer `//` over `/* */` when comments are needed.
